==Latin==
{{wikipedia|lang=la}}

===Etymology===
From [[Osco-Umbrian]], from {{proto|Italic|lukʷos|lang=la}}, metathesis of {{proto|Indo-European|wĺ̥kʷos|lang=la}}. Osco-Umbrian regularly has [[Proto-Indo-European]] */kʷ/ → /p/. Instead of expected *{{recons|volpos|lang=la}} (compare Latin *{{recons|volquus|lang=la}}), there is ''l''/''w'' metathesis, most likely to avoid conflation with {{term|volpes|volpēs|fox|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{la-noun|lupus|lupi|lupī|m|second}} (''feminine'' '''[[lupa]]''')

# A [[wolf]]
#: ''Homo homini '''lupus''' est.''
#:: Man is a '''wolf''' to man.

